author: Times-News
title: Prep roundup: Bulldogs, Eagles, Warriors, Red Devils post volleyball victories
text: Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 12:44 AM Updated at 3:54 PM Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 12:44 AM Updated at 3:54 PM Dinaisya Harrison led Williams High School with 15 kills, five digs and four aces as the Bulldogs rallied to defeat visiting McMichael in five sets Thursday night in Mid-State 3-A Conference volleyball. Williams won 14-25, 25-18, 21-25, 25-16, 16-14. Bella Huerta recorded 31 assists, six kills and four digs while KenzieVance added 20 digs for the Bulldogs (9-10 overall, 5-8 Mid-State 3-A). Rebecca Hunnicutt tallied five kills and five digs. Ashley Braxton finished with nine digs. Mekayla White had eight kills. Lanie Murdock added five kills and three assists. McMichael fell to 13-6, 10-4. ■ EASTERN ALAMANCE 3, ROCKINGHAM COUNTY 2: At Mebane, the Eagles rallied from a set down to defeat the Cougars 25-20, 20-25, 20-25, 25-8, 16-14 in the Mid-State 3-A. Katie Price led the Eagles (13-6, 9-4) with 32 assists. Ayanna Dawson recorded six blocks and three kills, while Jordan Crabbe served three aces. ■ GREENSBORO GRIMSLEY 3, SOUTHERN ALAMANCE 2: At Greensboro, the Whirlies earned an All Metro victory, defeating the Patriots 20-25, 25-23, 25-21, 23-25, 15-12. Taylor Hendrix recorded 26 assists for Southern Alamance (10-11, 4-4). Taylor Haney had 13 kills and five digs while Brooke Barham added 11 digs and eight kills. Skylar Doss finished with 22 digs. Nicole Byrd tallied nine kills and Haylie Shields had five kills. Allison Allred served four aces. ■ WESTERN ALAMANCE 3, EASTERN GUILFORD 0: At Elon, the Warriors swept the Wildcats in the Mid-State 3-A. Sarah Pittard had eight kills, five aces and three blocks to lead Western Alamance (11-7, 8-6). Hailey Stout tallied five kills and nine aces while Jessica Walker finished with five kills and three blocks. Eastern Guilford dropped to 3-17, 2-12. ■ GRAHAM 3, REIDSVILLE 0: At Graham, the Red Devils downed Reidsville 25-9, 25-10, 25-10 in the Mid-State 2-A Conference. Sydney McCann recorded four kills and six assists while Alexia Matias had 13 assists for the Red Devils (6-10, 6-2). Izlyn Law tallied 10 assists. Mercedes Roberson had seven kills. ■ CRESSET CHRISTIAN 3, THE BURLINGTON SCHOOL 0: The Spartans fell 25-13, 25-8, 25-17 in a non-conference match. Emma McQueen paced the Spartans (4-12) with 10 assists and seven digs. Deja Cousin tallied seven digs and five kills while Kelly Bender had three kills and three digs. Sarah Holt McCuiston had five digs and three blocks. Molina Williams had six digs. Cresset Christian improved to 19-6. Boys’ soccer At Graham, Caleb LaTour scored two second-half goals to help lead AlamanceChristianSchool to a 4-0 victory against Faith Christian in a North CarolinaChristian School Association game. Page 2 of 2 - The Warriors (12-2-1, 9-1) are in line to receive the No. 1 seed in the Western Region in next week’s state playoffs. Graham Doucette recorded two assists. Alex Briggs and Jonathan Brann scored the other goals. Drew Mathison recorded eight saves in goal for Faith Christian. By Times-News
